Key innovations include uncertainty-guided memory bank sampling and geometric priors for ambiguous regions. The approach aims to improve robustness and interpretability in applications like robotic manipulation and industrial automation. A recommended next step is to validate the method in a focused domain—such as robotic bin picking or surgical instrument tracking—to assess performance under real-world constraints.
